": "magistriõpe", "en": "master's studies"}, {"code": "doctoral", "et": "doktoriõpe", "en": "doctoral studies"}], "hours": {"lecture": 8, "practice": 0, "seminar": 8, "colloquium": 0, "web_learning": 0, "independent_work": 10, "individual_work": 0, "internship": 0}, "is_enlight_course": false}, "overview": {"study_languages": [{"code": "et", "et": "eesti keel", "en": "Estonian"}], "other_languages": [{"code": "en", "et": "inglise keel", "en": "English"}], "description": {"en": "The city is a pool of people and ideas, public and hidden habitats, benefits, and obstacles of urban life. It is divided into neighbourhoods that embrace a specific sense of belonging. Some of these are connected and woven together, some of them stand in isolation. This happens both by building physical borders and drawing personal boundaries. However, at the borderlines between regularity and disorder, between animal and plant neighbours, between those living on land and those living in the water, the playful connections take place. Such connections in the city are an inspiration to play with urban life.", "et": "Tänav sümboliseerib liikumist, kuid ka seda, mis püsib paigal ja jääb liiklusest kõrvale - avalikke ja peidetud elupaiku, kohatunnet, linnaelu hüvesid ja valupunkte. Mõni tänav ühendab, mõni lahutab. Linnast leiab nii korrakindla loogika kui ka seletamatuste rägastiku. Tänaval tõmbame füüsiliste piirete kõrvale ka isiklikke - mida tohib, mis on sünnis. Selle kõrval tasub teadlikult ringi vaadata ja leida üles piiripealne ruum, kus saavad kokku reeglite järgijad ja eirajad, naabrid looma- ja taimeriigist, kuival maal ja vees tegutsejate seast. Mõttevahetus, milles mängitakse mõttega tervemast ja mitmekesisemast linnaelust ja -ruumist."}, "objectives": [{"en": "Providing an overview of opportunities to create a healthier and more diverse urban life and space. Presenting possibilities for urban space development by crossing the boundaries of scientific disciplines.", "et": "Ülevaate andmine tervema ja mitmekesisemast linnaelu ja -ruumi loomise võimalustest.\nTutvustada linnaruumi arendamise võimalusi teadusdistsipliinide piire ületades."}], "learning_outcomes": [{"en": "A student who has completed this course will have an overview of:", "et": "Õppeaine läbinu omab ülevaadet:"}, {"en": "various aspects of creating a healthier and more diverse urban space,", "et": "tervema ja mitmekesisema linnaruumi loomise erinevatest aspektidest,"}, {"en": "possibilities for playful and modern solutions to urban sustainability issues", "et": "linnaelu kestlikkusprobleemide mängulise ja kaasaegse lahendamise võimalustest"}, {"en": "opportunities to design urban spaces as playful environments for children,", "et": "linnaruumi lastele mänguliseks keskkonnaks kujundamise võimalustest"}, {"en": "interdisciplinary collaboration in urban space development.", "et": "erinevate teadusdistsipliinide koostööst linnaruumi arendamisel"}], "notes": {}}, "grading": {"independent_work": {}, "grade_preconditions": {}, "grade_evaluation": {"et": "Aktiivne osalemine kõigil loengutel ja töötoas."}, "debt_elimination": {}, "assessment_scale": {"code": "pass", "et": "Eristamata (arv, m.arv, mi)", "en": "non-differentiated (pass, fail, not present)"}, "results_available_from": {}}, "resources": {"web_based": {"code": "3", "et": "lähiõpe", "en": "face-to-face learning"}, "is_moodle_connected": false}, "participants": {"lecturers": [{"person_uuid": "7c872456-f467-6fa4-8b38-04006432f0a1", "person_name": "Anto Aasa", "structural_unit": {"code": "LTOM02GR", "name": {"en": "Chair of Human Geography", "et": "inimgeograafia ja regionaalplaneerimise õppetool"}, "level": 4, "academic": false, "supports_continuous_learning": false, "parent_code": "LTOM02"}, "is_responsible": false, "is_teaching": true}, {"person_uuid": "45c4e13b-a442-6398-96ce-bf9ca537934d", "person_name": "Helen Sooväli-Sepping", "structural_unit": {"code": "LTOM02", "name": {"en": "Department of Geography", "et": "geograafia os